  "text": "Second, regarding actigraphy, while the raw data are very accurate in terms of time-stamped movements over extended periods (9-16 days), the periods of sleep are extracted from movement and not directly from brain activity, although the algorithms have been correlated with polysomnography [CITATION_1] . Therefore, timing of sleep start and sleep end may vary in accuracy depending on the individual patterns in relation to the pre-set sensitivity levels and thresholds, which will affect sleep latency, duration of sleep and periods of wake after sleep onset but not sleep fragmentation and activity levels because they are derived directly from activity counts without sensitivity thresholds.",
